ride_title: 30 min San Andres to Bailadero Ride
ride_description: We are departing San Andres and heading north on the main road in Anaga towards El Bailadero to reach the heart of the mountain. It is said that El Bailadero is named after the gathering place of witches who practiced magic and danced there.
Set yourself into motion in "the land of fire" at the world's final frontier. Soak in the sun, snowy mountain tops and wildlife in this vast and expansive landscape.
Take a ride through the classic tracks of the 2000s while you sweat it out on the Bike.

Enjoy the popular city sights, including Parc de la Ciutadella, Arc de Triomf, the colorful Torre Glòries, the unfinished Sagrada Familia (the jewel of Barcelona), and Park Güell before heading up Tibidabo hill to watch the sunset.

Joshua Tree National Park covers almost 800,000 acres of desert wilderness straddling the Mojave and Colorado deserts ... and you get to enjoy this magical landscape, characterized by rock formations,  all to yourself.
Ride on this stunning trail through forests bordering the Turnagain Arm inlet. Feast your eyes with spectacular scenic views
Enjoy the solitude of Iceland's Westfjords, as you ride along the coast towards the fishing town of Isafjörōur.
Ride high along the Gotthard Pass in the Swiss Alps, the mountain pass connecting northern and southern Switzerland.
Take a ride through the streets of London taking in iconic sites from Big Ben to Tower Bridge. Filmed by professionals on a closed course. Do not attempt to recreate.
Endless miles of vineyards and small quaint towns ... can you smell the fragrant aroma of vineyards all around you? Like their wines, this ride through Medoc is fine and elegant.

Treat yourself to this spectacular Norwegian scenic ride! You'll come across fjords, boulders, heathland and lush farmlands, and a few sheep on your way.
Journey over to Northern Italy as we head to Lago Di Garda. You'll be accompanied by blue skies, gorgeous mountains, tall lush trees and miles of scenic roadways.
Follow the single track trail around Prosser Reservoir near Donner Camp Picnic Area on this clear summer day.
Ride along the bike paths in the sunny city of Annecy. Explore the city center, parks, and ride alongside the Annecy Lake.
Discover France in a new light. We’re headed to Midi-Pyrénées to ride towards breathtaking mountain ranges, through quaint villages and alongside babbling brooks.
Ride among pink and lavender clouds as you rise and fall through winding crater roads of Haleakalā's National Park on the island of Maui.
Sweat it out through the desert as you explore the Canyonlands National Park. Carved from the Colorado River, you'll experience so much throughout the rocky terrain.

Explore Colorado's Front Range trails starting in Boulder with views of the Flat Irons and Eldorado Canyon. Then head up to White Ranch through the meadows where you may must catch a glimpse of Denver in the distance.
Meander through the suburban streets of modern day to the countryside. From there, seek out the historical architecture while you push yourself through the hills of Morbihan Brittany.

Take this chilled ride to visit the island, its village, and its pristine coastline. This ride offers it all: lush forests, jaw dropping ocean views, boats bobbing in the harbour past beautiful seaside houses.
